name: 贾里德·迈克尔·德莱尼
name_full: 贾里德·迈克尔·德莱尼 Jared Michael Delaney
introduction: Jared Michael Delaney is a playwright & actor based in Philadelphia, Pa. As an actor: off-Broadway(59e59); regional: Folger Theater, Arden Theatre Company, Philadelphia Theatre Company, Sierra Rep. Company, PA Shakespeare Festival, River Valley Rep, Walnut St Theatre, Lantern Theatre, Theatre Workshop of Nantucket, New Jersey Rep. Company, Theatre at Monmouth, Azuka Theatre and many others. Film: Kinderwald, A Man of No Importance, Head Space, numerous commercials & industrials. As a writer: His full-length play The Hand of Gaul was produced in 2013 (Inis Nua Theatre) and his play Noli Timere (Don't Be Afraid) premiered 2017 (Theatre Conspiracy). Readings: Paint It Black,You Devil, Strange Sun Theatre; Child of Lions, HRC Showcase Theatre and "Honorable Mention" New Works of Merit; The Cannibal of Ajax, Best Medicine Rep; Voyager One, New Jersey Repertory Company (April 2018)and semi-finalist for the Eugene O'Neill Theater Center's 2018 National Playwrights' Conference; Falstaff & the Endless Machine, semi-finalist for the inaugural Shakespeare's New Contemporaries competition. His short play "Fortune's Fool" was selected to be part of New Jersey Repertory Company's Theatre Brut Festival and will be published in a related anthology next fall. M.A. Theatre Arts, Villanova University. M.F.A., Stage/Screenwriting, Queens University of Charlotte. Member, AEA; Dramatists' Guild.
